I'm guessing at least some of this is due to a post I made in the last week or so suggesting Andrzej considering tempering his critiques of puzzles in the same way he might have wanted those who traumatized him about math to have tempered their critiques.

Other than I've been pondering the Golden Rule a lot these days, I'm not sure what frame of mind made it possible for me to do this without realizing it might be an embarrassment to Andrzej, but that's the way my mind was working that night at that time.

So I apologize for my lapse in judgement.  I'm really fond of all you guys, and really don't want to be offensive.

I would, however, maintain that the original question was not a bad one, and is the type we should all be posing to ourselves on occasion.

