@Connie
There are several children's librarians in our pantheon!  Guides to wonderful books (The Redwall series comes to mind) and resources.  When I was semi-retired, I subbed a while, and the day I was "the librarian" was truly a joy.  

When we were "stationed" in Fort Smith, Arkansas, in the mid-Fifties, The Carnegie Library was like a palace to me, but we were told that they did not issue library cards to Army families (because we moved away, eventually, of course.)  I was crushed, though...  In adulthood, upon moving to a new place, I do two things at once:  register to vote, and get a library card!

